$T(X) = sum_s A^s X A^s^dagger$, $X$ is the density matrix of the virtual state

$T(X_alpha) = lambda_alpha X_alpha$,

$lambda_alpha$ tells us how the mode $X_alpha$ evolves under the repeated application of the channel.

$T^n (X_alpha) = lambda_alpha^n X_alpha$

== Decay channel

eigenmodes with $|lambda| <1$

$||T^n (X_alpha)|| ~ |lambda|^n -> 0$

if $lambda$ is complex, $lambda = |lambda| e^(i theta)$, then $lambda^n =|lambda|^n e^(i n theta)$ $=>$ exponentially decay oscillations.

== Rotation channel

eigenmodes with $|lambda| = 1$

$lambda = e^(i theta)$, $T^n (X) = e^(i n theta) X$ does noit shrink the mode.